    "created_at": "2015-04-06T22:44:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-06T22:44:56Z",
    "body": "I'm still in favor of just making `io::Error` use `Arc` directly instead of `Box` (which still requires the `Sync` bound), because then I could just go back to calling `.clone()` on `io::Error` instead of using a custom `Error` type that pretends to be the underlying shared `io::Error`.\n",
